
[1]drudge

   DRUDGE, v.i. druj. To work hard; to labor in mean offices; to labor
   with toil and fatigue.

   In merriment did drudge and labor.

   DRUDGE, n. One who works hard, or labors with toil and fatigue; one who
                labors hard in servile employments; a slave.
